# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# ─── Conventional Commits 1.0 ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# type   Required. One of:
#          feat      a new feature for the user
#          fix       a bug fix for the user
#          docs      documentation only
#          style     formatting; no code change
#          refactor  code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#          perf      performance improvement
#          test      add or fix tests
#          build     build system or external dependencies (pyproject, uv.lock)
#          ci        CI configuration (GitHub Actions, etc.)
#          chore     other maintenance (no src or test changes)
#          revert    reverts a previous commit
#
# scope  Optional. Lowercase module / area name. Examples:
#          agent, memory, knowledge, edge, auth, ci, deps, docs
#
# subject  Required. Imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period.
#          Max ~50 chars. Examples:
#            ✓ feat(agent): add agentfactory contract
#            ✓ fix(memory): handle empty session payload
#            ✗ Added some agent code.
#
# body   Optional. Wrap at ~72 chars. Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW.
#        Separate from subject with a blank line.
#
# footer Optional. Wrap at ~72 chars. Used for:
#          - Breaking changes:   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#          - Issue references:   Refs: #123 / Closes: #123
#
# Lines starting with '#' are stripped by git.
